reviews.title: Korean Pronunciation
reviews.comment: Please include voice over or pronunciation lesson for the korean words. I already know english, so kindly consider this.  Diodict 3 has this feature. Also, please bring back the quiz cards with a funny person in it. It is much enjoyable to learn that way.  Thanks.
reviews.author: Jessa Gernale

reviews.title: Nice features missing in version 4
reviews.comment: Korran pronunciation feature being taken off is a huge issue. And the writing  function on the left column (like your korean dict) is taken off as well. Two useful tools that you should put it back for ur next upgrade.
reviews.author: Ee Way Teng

reviews.title: Handy communication tool
reviews.comment: Great little tool for helping explain more complex concepts between Korean and English speakers. One thing though, could you add some flash cards for learning Korean vocabulary? Thanks!
reviews.author: Hamish Moffatt

reviews.title: Now works on 4.1
reviews.comment: Now launches without crashing. Looks like a good dictionary from first glance. You won\'t be able to get a refund, the downloading of the dictionary files eats up your trial window. :: UPDATE-Version 4 is a big improvement and is much better looking. Thank you for the free upgrade from version 3! NOTE: There\'s only pronunciation for English, not Korean. I was hoping for Korean pronunciation since I\'m an English speaker learning Korean
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Best option for Android
reviews.comment: Most complete dictionary so far - not an easy task for Korean dictionaries, which tend to be quite lacking, even in print. I use it almost every day!
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: What happened to highlight function?
reviews.comment: After update to Dodict 4,the highlight function is gone. It used to be only a great function. I rather like Dodict version3 for studying. It seems like common internet version of dictionary. Please bring me back to the version3.Poor upgrade.From Android 4.1 (Galaxy note 2).
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Data
reviews.comment: Why does it keep downloading data everytime I open the app. It\'s a bug that slows the app down from running also will not work without a data connection fix for more stars
reviews.author: cornelius harris

reviews.title: can\'t use it.
reviews.comment: I tried splitting the app by saving it to my intenal sd but now it says I have to download all the files again.  but the most heartbreaking part is that it won\'t download the files. it cuts off the dl saying bad connection and closes. I\'m frustrated coz I just found a free offline app with 85mb but works fine without having to download again though it doesn\'t have any pronunciation.
reviews.author: cael tabucanon

reviews.title: Bring back Korean text-to-speech!!!!
reviews.comment: Bring back Korean text to speech!!! When I got a new phone it automatically updated me from version 3  to version 4 and so I lost Korean text to speech.  If you\'re going to upgrade me without my consent at least keep the same features! Those features are why I paid for version 3
reviews.author: Daemon Hobbs

reviews.title: No Korean Pronunciation
reviews.comment: Funny since the UI is all in English. Why is there no Korean pronunciation? I heard it was even in the app before but removed? WTF?
reviews.author: Chris Davaz

reviews.title: nexus s, JB
reviews.comment: after upgrading a support of korean pronunciation disappeared. is it upgrading?
reviews.author: Victor Parkhomenko

reviews.title: Needs some updates
reviews.comment: No transition animation like on iOS and when scrolling up and down, the screen blinks at times. Please fix it.
reviews.author: Jung Soo Kim

reviews.title: Korean pronunciation
reviews.comment: What happen to Korean pronunciation after latest update?
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Great, for two minutes
reviews.comment: This is a really helpful dictionary, for the two minutes it works.  After that is crashes.  Try to search for a word, crashes.  Try to scroll to the word and click on it, crashes.  Try to open it, crashes.  A two legged table on a fishing boat in the mid-Atlantic is more stable.  Also takes hours to download all the files.  Literally, hours.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Used to be very good...
reviews.comment: When I first bought this on my SG S2, it worked great but after the last and the latest android updates, it takes ages to download library files and keeps crashing when it about to initialize the files. This is in the newest android ver 4.0.4 ...PLZ fix it
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Great... when it works
reviews.comment: I love being able to easily search, especially using voice and Korean gestures.  BUT the app can\'t work for more than a minute before crashing.  I tried it on both Galaxy Nexus and Nexus 7, each running Android 4.1, and the same thing happened on both.  The dictionary is therefore just about unuseable.  If an update fixes the problem this dictionary gets five stars.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: The mediocre dictionary
reviews.comment: Diodict does not live up to its claim of greatness, it is a very unexciting standard dictionary not really taking advantage of the interactive medium. It is significantly slower, more cumbersome and lacking many of the useful features that say, the free app kotoba for ios has. As such the price is a robbery. Sadly the other korean dictionaries for android seems to be as bad, so you may not have a choice.
reviews.author: A Google User
